But, for all that, I should like you to write to her yourself, and tell her not to think there is anything either so important, or so insignificant, as to seem to me either difficult, or beneath my dignity. Anything I may have to do in relation to your affairs I shall regard as a labour of love and an honour to myself. As to Dionysius, as you are my friend, wind up the business ; whatever pledge you have given him, Ι shall redeem it. If, however, he proves himself a scoundrel (as he is), you will lead him captive in your triumph. Perdition seize the Dalmatians, who are worrying you! But, as you say, they will soon be taken, and so shed lustre on your exploits 3 for they have always been accounted
